title: Orbital Composites leans into space market
summary: Orbital Composites is gaining traction in the emerging in-space servicing, assembly and manufacturing sector thanks to government contracts and partnerships.

title: Ramon.Space reveals partnership with Foxconn subsidiary Ingrasys
summary: Ramon.Space announced a strategic partnership June 20 with Foxconn subsidiary Ingrasys aimed at high-volume production of satellite computing technology.

title: Boeing CEO says company still committed to Starliner
summary: The chief executive of Boeing says his company is still committed to the CST-100 Starliner commercial crew vehicle despite the latest problems that have further delayed the program.

title: Indonesia’s Satria-1 deploys solar panels ahead of geostationary trip
summary: Indonesia’s Satria-1 broadband satellite deployed its solar panels after launching on a SpaceX Falcon 9 to geosynchronous transfer orbit over the weekend, manufacturer Thales Alenia Space said June 19.

title: Rocket Lab launches first HASTE mission
summary: Launching at 9:24 PM ET on June 17th (01:24 UTC June 18th), the first Rocket Lab HASTE launch vehicle successfully lifted off...

title: Skyrora Tests First 3D Printed Rocket Engine
summary: Skyrora, a UK-based space company, is conducting a series of full-duration tests to qualify the updated design of its 70kN engine for its inaugural commercial orbital launch.

title: Cassini data reveals the presence of phosphorus in Enceladus’ ocean plumes
summary: A team of scientists, using archival data from NASA’s now-retired Cassini mission, has discovered the presence of phosphorus in the massive plumes of water being ejected from the southern regions of Saturn’s moon Enceladus. Phosphorus — a chemical element essential for life and often considered a building block for life — is locked inside of salt-rich ice grains ejected in these plumes.

title: China attracts moon base partners, outlines project timelines
summary: China says a number of countries have committed to join its International Lunar Research Station moon base initiative.

title: Space Development Agency’s missile warning satellites transmit first images
summary: The U.S. Space Force’s Space Development Agency said it received initial images from its first missile-warning satellites launched April 2 to low Earth orbit.

title: Kuva Space wins 5 million euro award for hyperspectral data
summary: Kuva Space plans to launch four microsatellites in 2024 and to deploy as many as 100 satellites by 2030.
